cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with classification/recognition via neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new metric for classification that is based on a semantically meaningful hierarchy of classes, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of an ultrametric tree, which is a concept commonly used in neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE).
